originalText.text: Amazingly friendly staff. I primarily stop here to grab a quick üçª on the way home. I must say the daily rotation of beer on tap is always a pleasant surprise. They offer plenty of gluten free options in the beer department. Wine selection is excellent. If you like liquor is also an option. There is a wide variety of snacks as well as baked goods. If you find yourself passing by in the morning make sure to grab a coffee and one of their delicious morning Glory muffins for a great start to the day. The staff will remember your order and have it started for you when they see you everything the store.

originalText.text: My family and I had an uncomfortable experience here. While my parents tried to carry me to the bathroom (I have a medical illness so I need assistance to move), an employee literally yelled at us. She screamed that we weren‚Äôt allowed to use their restrooms and that we had to go outside. We understood that the protocol may be different due to covid but the screaming while I was clearly having a medical issue (which we also told her about) was just a bit much. She could have just put up a sign with that information, told us with respect in a calm voice, or even offered to assist us in showing us the way. We tried to move out of her way as she was so quickly agitated. However, it was difficult with the medical issue I have. She eventually moved out the way so we could go out side to the trailer bathrooms but this was just a very uncomfortable experience. We still bought the items we sought out to buy at this store, but this experience turned me off. I‚Äôd like to not return here.

originalText.text: The positive - love the selection. The negative - the pricing is truly offensive, even in the context of Grand Central. Hill Rock whiskey for $170, average price is 90-100. $11 for a can of Finback been, normal 4 pack is $18. I could go on. I'd also add the staff could back off the sales pressure a bit. It's really a shame, since the opportunity to buy local goods in Grand Central is appealing and has drawn me in to the store more than once - but without fail, I always leave empty handed.
